---
description: Enforce frontend pseudo-package boundaries and import direction.
globs: apps/frontend/**/*.{ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: false
---
# Frontend Architecture Boundaries

- Treat `apps/frontend/app/src` as pseudo-packages:
  - `api`
  - `components`
  - `providers`
  - `utils`
  - `schemas`
  - `types`
  - `__fixtures__`
  - `storybook`
  - `routes`
- Use `@zanshin/*` aliases for cross-package imports instead of relative deep paths.
- Route modules in `app/src/routes` may import from `@zanshin/*`.
- Non-route packages must not import from `app/src/routes`.
- Each pseudo-package should expose a public entrypoint (`index.ts`/`index.tsx`) and consumers should prefer that entrypoint.
- Keep package responsibilities strict:
  - `api` exports request clients/contracts only
  - `providers` exports providers/state adapters only
  - `components` exports presentational/container UI components only
  - `schemas` exports validation schemas only
  - `types` exports type aliases only
  - `utils` exports pure utility/runtime helpers only
- Avoid circular dependencies; run and keep `madge` circular checks green.
